<p class="">With regard to capital investment, if we look across the Atlantic we find that in 1951 the American railways expended no less than 1,413 million dollars on capital investment, which is, <span id="1106" class="column-number" data-column-number="1106"></span> approximately, £504,225,000, whereas only £72 million was authorised in this country for the British Transport Commission. If railways are to contribute—</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-311a0b98-c9dd-4974-aa95-ed734b3ec17b" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
