<p class="">My right hon. Friend the Prime Minister on one occasion in this House said he felt at a certain disadvantage through not having a blackboard. I feel under the same disadvantage at the moment, but if the hon. Gentleman, who is always extremely fair in controversy, would follow those figures again when he sees them in HANSARD tomorrow morning, he will find that I have made a perfectly correct calculation.<p></p> This debate has been of great value in giving an airing to a problem which is causing considerable heart searching in various parts of the country.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
